animals_changed.name: Diamond
animals_changed.description_old: Diamond has a lot of personality filled with wiggles and cuddles! She seems to really enjoy hanging out with her people. She may jump at first greetings because she gets excited, but she calms down once she is out and about on leash. Diamond's favorite things are balls and chew toys! She can keep herself entertained for awhile. She's a snuggler, so expect this girl to keep you company when you need it the most.

animals_changed.name: Marco
animals_changed.description_old:
Meet Marco – your pint-sized copilot and professional snuggler! Marco is a one-year-old sweetheart who has somehow been overlooked at the shelter since August… which honestly just means his perfect people haven’t found him yet.

This little guy loves his humans and shows it by wagging his tail and leaning in for cozy cuddles. He’s tuned-in, affectionate, and happiest when he’s included in the fun – whether that’s a family movie night or a quick errand in the car (his car manners are A++).

Marco has done well meeting older kids visiting campus – he's a little playful, a little goofy, and very ready to be someone’s loyal sidekick. He’s a compact lovebug who will make your heart feel full every day. If you’re looking for a smallish best friend with a big heart… Marco’s your guy. 

Reach out to orangedotcrew@gmail.com to kickstart Marco's heartwarming journey. For more delightful updates, follow Orange Dot Crew on Facebook and Instagram.

animals_changed.description_new: Rocky is a very sweet, chatty kitten who loves wrestling with his siblings and cuddling with you! He is the most vocal of his litter. He is curious about everything that is happening, and will tell you all about it! He has also expressed interest in becoming a shoulder cat, so he can keep an eye on what you're doing. When he is done exploring (or wrestling!), he would like to curl up on your lap and purr!

animals_changed.name: Daisy
animals_changed.description_old: While she's the smallest of her litter, she can hold her own in the kitten wrestling matches! She loves playing, but even more, would love to become your lap cat! She is very sweet and cuddly!
animals_changed.description_new: While Daisy is the smallest of her litter, she can match the bigger kittens for energy and purrr-sonality! She loves playing, but even more, would love to become your lap cat! She is very sweet and cuddly, and will give you a little bath while she's cleaning herself. She has the prettiest coat colors, with a little bit of tortoiseshell in her tabby!

animals_changed.name: Pumpkin
animals_changed.description_old: Pumpki is the typical orange cat. Playful, a little crazy but loves his humans passionately. Ready to go home to his family Dec 3rd.
animals_changed.description_new: Pumpkin is playful, loves shoulder rides, and is happiest napping in a lap. Ready for his new home on December 3rd.

animals_changed.name: Gumdrop
animals_changed.description_old: Gumdrop is all wiggles and zoomies! He's a young guy who loves to run around in the play yard and get all that energy out. He seems housetrained and listens to direction. He's working on his leash skills (he doesn't seem to know his own strength). This handsome boy is ready for his freedom from kennel life!

animals_changed.name: Melo
animals_changed.description_old: Melo is a big cuddle bug! He's loving, patient and will give you hugs. His favorite things (besides snuggling with his people) might be playing catch and going on outdoor adventures. He loves his walks! Melo also has good experience getting along with other dogs and seems to enjoy their company. He's a crate trained all around very good boy ready for a home that matches his winning personality!

animals_changed.name: Timmy
animals_changed.description_old: Timmy is a tiny shepherd dreamboat. He is adorable and sweet. He looks right at you, sticks to your side, and asks for hugs. He is laid back for such a young little pup. He is paired with a dog friend and should be snapped up quick. He's perfect.

animals_changed.name: Princess Peach
animals_changed.description_old: Meet Princess Peach! She really wants you to because she loves new friends. This girl enjoys walks and play time with her friends, and if you give her a toy to carry around it will truly make her day! Princess Peach seems housetrained and crate trained. She's ready to take on the world with a toy in her mouth and a friend by her side, so say "hello" to this girl today!

animals_changed.name: Priscilla
animals_changed.description_old:
Priscilla may be a little shy at first, but she warms up quickly—especially if you have treats! Once she’s comfortable, she turns into the snuggliest, cuddliest, kissiest girl you’ve ever met. She’s incredibly gentle, with no mouthing or nipping, just pure sweetness.


When playtime arrives, she loves chasing toys around the yard and zooming happily after anything that bounces. She also walks beautifully on leash and enjoys exploring the world by your side.


Priscilla is ready to find her forever family—one that will give her the love and patience she deserves. Could that be you?

Come meet her and fall in love!

animals_changed.name: Buttercup
animals_changed.description_new:
Meet Buttercup — the sweetest soul you’ll ever meet.


This gentle, affectionate pittie came to us thanks to a kind Good Samaritan after she was found abandoned with her five puppies. Even on her first day, Buttercup showed us who she is at heart: calm, trusting, and endlessly loving. She allowed strangers to carry her and handle her puppies without a hint of worry — a true testament to her gentle nature.


Her pups, already old enough to be weaned, returned to their finder and are quickly finding homes. Buttercup, however, stayed with us so we could care for an injury to her left front leg that left her a bit lame. X-rays showed no fractures, and with rest, medication, and TLC, she has made a remarkable recovery.


Now Buttercup is ready to take the next step: a foster or adoptive home of her very own.

She has quickly become a staff and volunteer favorite — the kind of dog people go out of their way to visit because she brightens everyone’s day. We would love nothing more than to see her curled up on a soft bed in a real home instead of a kennel.


If you're looking for a gentle, loving companion who will melt your heart, Buttercup is your girl. Come meet her and see why we all adore her.

animals_changed.name: Waverly
animals_changed.description_new:
Waverly is a super mellow, easygoing, sweet, and well-trained dog.

She loves people and listens SO well. She is house-trained and non-destructive. She walks perfectly on a leash and doesn't react at all to other dogs or passersby (besides tail wags!).

She was found as a stray, caring for her young puppies, and now it's her turn to be cared for in her forever home!

animals_changed.name: Chico
animals_changed.description_new: Chico found his way into the care of community member as a stray pup running loose, but they were not able to keep him long term. Chico is a gentle guy who is still learning to walk on leash. He absolutely loves play time outside in a fenced area and has enjoyed the company of his human and canine friends. Chico may be shy at first, but his loving, silly personality comes out pretty quickly! He's affectionate and will listen to his person and follow their lead. This boy is smart and ready to learn all about life in a new home.

animals_changed.name: Lelee
animals_changed.description_old:
Lelee is a sweet, calm, and lovable companion looking for her perfect forever home. With her gentle, low-to-medium energy, she’s the ideal pup for someone who wants a peaceful, steady friend by their side. She walks beautifully on leash—no pulling, just happy strolls and tail wags all the way.

Lelee is house trained and knows basic commands (and maybe even more than she lets on!). She prefers to be the only pet in the home so she can soak up all the love, but she does great meeting other dogs or cats politely on leash outside the home.

This always-smiling girl is ready to bring warmth, joy, and endless tail wags to her new family.

Come meet her today—she can’t wait!

animals_changed.name: Panda
animals_changed.description_old: Hi there! My name's Panda, and I'm a big, lanky, goofy boy with a whole lot of love to give. My foster dad calls me their "wormy-squirmy guy" because I wiggle and flop around with joy, especially when I'm rolling over for belly rubs. I'm full of playful energy and would be happiest in a home with another dog who loves to play as much as I do. Fetch is one of my favorite games, and I never say no to splashing around in the water! After playtime, I'm always ready to snuggle up close; I'm just as much of a cuddle bug as I am a goofball. I've got good manners too! I walk nicely on a loose leash, I take treats gently, and I already know "sit" and "stay." More than anything, I really want to please you and be your loyal companion. If you're looking for a fun-loving, affectionate boy who will keep you laughing, join you on adventures, and then curl up for cuddle time, I think we might be the perfect match. I can't wait to meet my forever family!
animals_changed.description_new:
I’m a big, lanky, wormy, squirmy boy with a heart of gold and legs for days!

I’m a playful goofball who loves to have fun, and I’d be over the moon to have another playful dog friend in my new home. I adore romping around, wrestling, playing chase, and especially playing fetch—throw the ball, and I’m on it! I also really enjoy water, so kiddie pools, sprinklers, or creek adventures are totally my thing.

Walks are one of my favorite parts of the day. I walk loosely on the leash and love to trot right alongside you, whether we’re out for a casual stroll or a nice run. I’m a good boy who wants to obey; I already know sit and stay, and I’m eager to learn more. I take treats very gently, so training time is fun and easy with me.

I’m currently being taken care of by my foster dad, and I really love getting attention and affection. When you start petting me, I tend to flop dramatically onto the ground and roll over to show you my belly...it’s my specialty move! I’m a big sweetheart who just wants to be close, soak up love, and be your goofy sidekick.

If you’re looking for a sweet, silly, water-loving best friend with a big heart, goofy grin, and a lot of love for snacks, I’m your guy!

animals_changed.name: Mr. Muffin
animals_changed.description_old:
Meet Mr. Muffin — the strong, silent type with a heart of gold. This independent and loving boy is house trained, easygoing, and carries himself with quiet confidence. Once you earn his trust, his playful, gentle side shines through — especially when he’s getting pampered with chest scratches, temple massages, or a good brushing (his absolute favorite!).

Volunteers can’t help but fall for Mr. Muffin’s calm, soulful presence — he’s the kind of dog that makes you wish your home could fit “just one more.” On park outings, he takes everything in stride, relaxed and well-mannered amid all the activity. Mr. Muffin is also treat-motivated and proudly shows off his “sit” on command.

If you’re looking for a steady, affectionate companion who brings peace, loyalty, and quiet joy, Muffin might just be your perfect match.
